# <%= appName %> — MVC Architecture

Model-View-Controller separation for <%= backend %> APIs.

## Layers

| Layer | Path | Responsibility |
|-------|------|----------------|
| Controllers | `src/controllers/` | HTTP request/response, status codes, validation entry |
| Services | `src/services/` | Business logic and orchestration |
| Models | `src/models/` | Data shapes and domain types |
| DTOs | `src/dto/` | Request/response transfer objects |
| Middleware | `src/middleware/` | Cross-cutting HTTP concerns |

## Dependency flow

```
HTTP Request → Controller → Service → Repository/Model → Response
```

Controllers **must not** import database drivers or ORM clients directly.

## Commands

```bash
my make controller <name>
my make service <name>
my make model <name> --fields name:string
```

See `.architecture/MODULE_BOUNDARIES.md` for import rules.
